  "technical_info": {
    "content": [
      "According to the Open Packaging Format 2.0 specification, NCX files should be created with a corresponding .OPF file, which contains the linear reading order and other eBook metadata.",
      "NOTE: Since NCX files are saved in an XML format, they can be viewed and edited with a text editor."
    ]
  },
  "more_information": {
    "description": [
      "Table of contents file created according to the XML-based Open Packaging Format (OPF) standard, which is part of the EPUB eBook specification; stores the document title and author, as well as the navigation points for the eBook; used as part of an overall .EPUB archive."
    ]
